<SLUG> BC-OSTLER-COLUMN-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 BIG GUN CARRIED IN VIOLIN CASE  &HT;     By SCOTT OSTLER 
 &HT;     c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ A violin with an entourage?
</P>
<P>
   Yes, here it comes: ``Il Cannone'' (The Cannon), a 250-year-old
violin that belonged to Nicolo Paganini, who was the Jimi Hendrix
of 19th century fiddling.
</P>
<P>
   Il Cannone will be played by Eugene Fodor on Tuesday night in a
benefit at the Herbst.
</P>
<P>
   The violin is traveling from its home in Genoa and will be
accompanied on the trip by its custodian, along with the Genoa
chief of police and five other people.
</P>
<P>
   I hear Il Cannone is demanding its own hotel suite, a Lemon
Pledge rubdown and a gram of fresh Peruvian rosin.
</P>
<P>
   MAYOR WILLIE BROWN stops by the Boom Boom Room one night on his
appointed rounds o' da town.
</P>
<P>
   Bartender Michael Krouse buttonholes the mayor, tells him about
a project. Krouse wants to paint a mural on the outside wall of the
Boom Boom, facing Geary, a tribute to the Fillmore District's rich
musical heritage. Would the city help finance the work?
</P>
<P>
   Mayor says he'll see what he can do. Right.
</P>
<P>
   Couple months later, Michael gets a grant for $13,500 from the
office of Neighborhood Beautification.
</P>
<P>
   Whattaya know, city government works for the little guy,
sometimes. And Krouse didn't even have to pay consultant Jack Davis
$330,000 to lobby the mayor for the grant.
</P>
<P>
   GHOST OF A CHANCE: Somebody in the Haight apparently is
disenchanted with the choices in the upcoming mayoral election. The
home is displaying a very large vintage sign: ``Moscone for
mayor.''
</P>
<P>
   FORGET CAT-SCANS. Here's how we'll know if 49er QB Steve Young
has head damage:
</P>
<P>
   A scientific study found a correlation between brain damage and
impaired morals, so a reader named Doc says to look for warning
signs: Mormon Steve swilling Coke on the sidelines.
</P>
<P>
   ``ROSES ARE RED, and lovely forivver/On the list of top grads I
guess I'm just chopped liver.''
</P>
<P>
   The Lowell High alums published a directory that includes ``A
Sampling of Grads,'' high achievers in every walk of life.
</P>
<P>
   Missing: A poet. And at least one Lowell alum, Robert Peterson,
is a widely acclaimed poet.
</P>
<P>
   James Russell Lowell would consider the oversight poetic
injustice.
</P>
<P>
   THEY'LL BE SHIFTING into a higher gear Monday night at the
Transmission Theater, at a benefit blowout for Rudy Castro, famed
big-band leader.
</P>
<P>
   On the Bay Area musical family tree, Rudy's a huge branch. His
rehearsal big band has been cranking for half this century,
grooming a huge roster of great musicians and singers. Rudy is 80,
chair-bound after a stroke last year.
</P>
<P>
   If half of Rudy's pupils and friends show, and they will, Monday
night will go down in swing/big-band legend.
</P>
<P>
   MORE VIOLIN NEWS: Hey, wasn't that Sting front-rowing at the
symphony last night? Yes, he came to hear his new buddy, violinst
Kennedy, who is guest-virtuosoing with the symph orchestra this
week.
</P>
<P>
   Kennedy, the artist formerly known as Nigel Kennedy, is a
strange character who grooves with the symphony, then hits the
city's backstreet clubs and jams all night with the fellas.
</P>
<P>
   Sting was playing in Berkeley, and the two happened to meet, hit
it off and made plans to rip up the city last night.
</P>
<P>
   Somebody please hand Kennedy ``Il Cannone,'' and jump back.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Now accepting applications &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Fight Club &LR;
</P>
<P>
   And speaking of Fight Club, when  &UR; is  &LR; the next bare-knuckles
mayoral debate?
</P>
<P>
   A TOMATO DETECTOR will be used at the door for next Wednesday
night's Commonwealth Club event.
</P>
<P>
   Guest speaker: Michael Burns, Muni general manager. His topic:
``Muni in the Millennium.''
</P>
<P>
   Some questions Burns might be called upon to field:
</P>
<P>
   -- Which millennium will Muni be entering?
</P>
<P>
   -- How many more millennia will I have to wait for my freakin'
bus?
</P>
<P>
   -- Millennium? Did Willie say he'd fix Muni in 100  &UR; years? &LR;
</P>
<P>
   -- Can I get a transfer to another speech?
</P>
</TEXT>
