<P>
   NYHAN-COLUMN (Undated) -- A salute to David Riesman, now 90, who
wrote ``The Lonely Crowd,'' which told Americans who we are and why
we are that way. By David Nyhan. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   JACKSON-COLUMN (Undated) _ Philip Morris is playing us all for
Bozos. Last week the cigarette maker unveiled a Web page that,
after decades of denials and lies, admitted that the company's
products might cause a few problems for consumers, like, um,
cancer. By Derrick Jackson. 850 words.
</P>
