   &UR; LIFESTYLE (l) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FRANCO-NEW ENGLAND (Undated) _ As Franco-Americans in New
England examine the state of their culture, they use a common word
to discuss their half-hidden presence: ``la survivance,'' which
carries connotations of both preservation and persistence. By
Michael Kenney. 2,100 words. Two takes. Photo
</P>
<P>
   BEAM-COLUMN (Undated) -- The fallout from the Boston museum
firings crosses the pond. By Alex Beam. 700 words.
</P>
