   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-STRAIGHT (Undated) _ In a 180-degree turn from the
surrealistic weirdness of his previous films, David Lynch makes
simplicity seem pure, eloquent, and deeply moving in ``The Straight
Story. By Jay Carr. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-BOYS (Undated) _ ``In Cold Blood,'' ``Badlands,'' ``The
Executioner's Song,'' and now, joining those grisly milestones on
the heartland hit list, and every bit their equal, is ``Boys Don't
Cry.'' By Jay Carr. 1,000 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-DEAD (Undated) _ ``Bringing Out the Dead,'' Martin
Scorsese's film about EMS drivers, isn't a thrill ride. It's a soul
ride. By Jay Carr. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-BESTMAN (Undated) _ Malcolm D. Lee's ``The Best Man'' is a
romantic comedy that gets the important things right. By Jay Carr.
600 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-ROSIE (Undated) _ ``Rosie,'' from a new Belgian director,
Patrice Toye, is a devastatingly understated powerhouse of a film.
By Jay Carr. 470 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-SHOTS (Undated) _ Beneath its glitz, poses, pub crawlers,
and club prowlers, ``Body Shots'' is an old-fashioned morality tale
whose central event is a date rape at the end of an evening spent
by four couples. By Jim Carr. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-BATS (Undated) _ ``Bats'' is a reassuring little movie: It
proves that if you use the latest computerized technology, and you
really, really try, you can make a film that's just as cheesy as
yesteryear's B-movies. By Jay Carr. 440 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-CRAZY (Undated) _ Juggling Southern gothic eccentricity
and civil rights advocacy, ``Crazy in Alabama'' represents a
challenging directing debut for Antonio Banderas. To his credit, he
and the film land on their feet. By Jay Carr.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIE-TANGO (Undated) _ ``Three to Tango'' trips early and never
gets up off the floor. By Jay Carr.
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-HICK-HOP (Undated) _ The brave new world of hick-hop mixes
hip-hop, classic rock, and country in ways that neither Grandmaster
Flash nor Hank Williams could have imagined. It's the creation of a
27-year-old bundle of contradictions known as Kid Rock. By Steve
Morse. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-ROCK (Undated) _ The Stone Temple Pilots regroup and
salvage the chemistry that has made it a hard-rock powerhouse. By
Steve Morse. 1,200 words.
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-DOG (Undated) _ It can sometimes be difficult to climb the
mountain of thought in Walter Mosley new novel, ``Walkin' the
Dog,'' but its meaning and style of expression make it a rewarding
exercise. By Michael Prager. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
