   JASPER-DAD (Geneva, Ohio) _ Shawn Berry's father hadn't seen him
since he was a toddler, but he was hoping to see him last summer.
Louis, Shawn's older brother, had made contact with their long-lost
dad, Louis Hezebicks, in a suburb of Cleveland. Louis told his dad
about Shawn's beat-up old pickup truck and told him they would
drive up to see him sometime. The next time Hezebicks heard about
the truck was on the news, in a report about a black man chained to
the vehicle and dragged to his death on East Texas road. By RICHARD
STEWART. (Filed Friday.)
