year since Hurricane Mitch. Amid the often sluggish and sometimes
helter-skelter reconstruction effort, Hondurans and foreigners have
donated money in hopes of remaking, rather than merely restoring,
the world that Mitch unhinged. By DUDLEY ALTHAUS. (Photos available
on the NYT database.)
