waste to this country, Honduras still swirls with talk of a new
society that will rise from the rubble. No idea reaches further
toward that envisioned new dawn, perhaps, than Vida Nueva, a
sprawling development of ticky-tacky rows of houses set in a cow
pasture outside the industrial city of San Pedro Sula. By DUDLEY
ALTHAUS.
