80 years ago and Bill Clinton's recent loss on the nuclear test ban
treaty. In both instances, the president was a victim of his own
stubbornness as well as the obstructionist tactics of his
Republican opponents. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON. (Filed Wednesday.)
