</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ I have nothing in common with Pam Houston, the Arctic
musher; or Pam Houston, the Salmon River rafter; or Pam Houston,
the Himalayan trekker. But Pam Houston, the person? We are kindred
spirits. I came to this conclusion five years ago while reading
Houston's first book of short stories, ``Cowboys Are My Weakness,''
which describes in raw, wrenching and hilarious detail several
women's unsuccessful romantic interludes with a series of
