has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-GREGORY PECK &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Gregory Peck came from a golden age in
Hollywood when he and his contemporaries _ Henry Fonda, John Wayne,
Jimmy Stewart and Cary Grant _ captivated moviegoers with a
combination of charm, wit, machismo and screen presence. Peck was
the most versatile of all, starring in roles that demonstrated his
wide acting range. He is in Fort Worth as part of the Fort Worth
Film Festival, which will feature some of his films Saturday, and
starring in a one-man stage show Saturday afternoon at the Bass
Performance Hall. Peck also is the subject of a cable TV special,
``A Conversation with Gregory Peck,'' airing this month on TMC. By
ELVIS MITCHELL. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   C O M M E N T A R Y &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LABBE-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ It was clear this wasn't going to be a run-of-the-mill
professional seminar when the CEO of a non-profit group created to
invest billions of public dollars complained about having to
conduct business in the open. Journalists from across the state
convened in Austin earlier this month for the annual Freedom of
Information conference sponsored by the Freedom of Information
Foundation of Texas. This year's meeting was titled Access 2000 and
topics ranged from how the Internet is affecting access to
information to horror stories from reporters and citizens who had
the devil of a time getting their hands on what is supposed to be
public information. By J.R. LABBE. Story has moved in ``k''
commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Sooner or later, it's bound to happen. Some candidate
will drop out of the race for the Republican presidential
nomination and will not blame his failure on the front-runner's
fund raising. On second thought, maybe it won't happen. Maybe the
money thing is just too convenient an excuse. Even Elizabeth Dole
fell into the trap the other day when she shut down a presidential
campaign that was going nowhere fast. By BILL THOMPSON. Story has
moved in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
