budget negotiators say they are close to agreeing on a budget deal
that is palatable to both Democrats and Republicans. But even as
the negotiators were at work, congressional Republicans were
attacking President Clinton as a bid-spending liberal intent on
paying for programs by raising taxes. By GREG McDONALD. (Already
filed.)
