lower prices on goods. The pricing scheme is known as pooling, and
it gives sellers a certain number of committed buyers in exchange
for a lower price. How possible was this before the advent of the
Internet? Is this a unique pricing scheme, and will it catch on
like PriceLine.com did? By Jason Cohen (will move in the ``f''
