Lori Stassi at (818) 713-3705.
</P>
<P>
   RUBEN-LAUSD (Los Angeles) _ With the Los Angeles school board
expected to ratify its decision removing Superintendent Ruben
Zacarias from day-to-day oversight of the district, hundreds of
parents rally in support of the schools chief. Elected officials at
the rally included state Sen. Richard Polanco, D-Los Angeles,
county Supervisor Gloria Molina, L.A. City Council members Jackie
Goldberg, Rita Walters, Nate Holden and Mike Hernandez, and school
board member Victoria Castro. Polanco and Castro contributed $1,000
apiece to advertise the rally and bus people in for it. Other
contributors included MALDEF, Rep. Xavier Becerra, D-Los Angeles,
and City Councilman Nick Pacheco. By Sherry Joe Crosby (will move
on the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news wires)
</P>
<P>
   .
</P>
<P>
   UFO-BOOK (Los Angeles) _ Topanga Canyon is a veritable Roswell,
N.M., when it comes to unidentified flying objects. The author of
the ``U.F.O.s Over Topanga'' will speak and sign books at Barnes
and Noble in Calabasas. By Jason Kandel (will move on the ``a''
national and ``n'' California news wires)
</P>
<P>
   .
</P>
<P>
   STAPLES-TRAFFIC (Los Angeles) _ Sensitive to concerns about
traffic jams at the Staples Center, the Los Angeles City Council
considers ordering aerial pictures taken of traffic over a six-hour
period on Nov. 3 to look at traffic patterns. It's a Wednesday,
checking if it's a game day. By Rick Orlov (will move on the ``a''
national and ``n'' California news wires)
</P>
<P>
   FANTASIA-2000 (Los Angeles) _ Walt Disney Co. announced the 70
theaters worldwide where it will show ``Fantasia/2000'' beginning
Jan. 1. Four Southern California sites were selected. By Dave
McNary (will move on the ``a'' national, the ``n'' California and
``f'' financial news wire)
