<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-22 22:11 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5708 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u s BC-BKN-BARKLEY-RETIREMEN     10-22 0887
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-BARKLEY-RETIREMENT-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
Barkley to announce retirement Sunday
<TEXT>
<P>
   By MICHAEL MURPHY &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Houston Chronicle
</P>
<P>
   The Rockets' Charles Barkley, one of the most popular players in
NBA history, will announce his retirement Sunday, effective at the
end of the 1999-2000 season.
</P>
<P>
   Barkley, 36, will make the announcement in Birmingham, Ala., at
halftime of Sunday's preseason game against the Detroit Pistons.
Birmingham is less than a 20-minute drive from Barkley's hometown
of Leeds, Ala.
</P>
<P>
   Even though he has threatened to retire several times over the
past few years, Barkley insists this season will be it for him.
This will be his 16th NBA season.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's just time,'' said Barkley, who has been upgraded to
questionable for Sunday's game after missing the last four
preseason games with tendinitis in his right elbow. ``It's time.
That's it. I'm not going to answer any more questions about it.
It's just time.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know what I'm going to do (after he retires). I might
just take some time off. But I'm making it official Sunday. I'm
announcing it there (in Birmingham) because that's my hometown, and
I'll have a lot of family and friends there. This is my last year,
period. I don't care how well I'm playing _ this is it. I want to
get it over with, and that's it. I'm looking forward to it.''
</P>
<P>
   The NBA has to feel otherwise.
</P>
<P>
   Barkley has long been one of the league's top draws, especially
internationally. He was on the original Dream Team, playing with
Michael Jordan, Larry Bird and Magic Johnson on the juggernaut that
won the gold medal at the 1992 Olympics in Barcelona.
</P>
<P>
   In 1996, Barkley, then with the Phoenix Suns, teamed with
current Rockets teammate Hakeem Olajuwon on the Olympic basketball
team that won a gold medal in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   ``If Charles has decided that this is his last season, then we
should all relish one more chance to be entertained by one of the
most spectacular players in NBA history,'' NBA deputy commissioner
Russ Granik said. ``Charles is certainly a one-of-a-kind
personality, but first and foremost, he is a truly great talent on
the court.''
</P>
<P>
   Rockets owner Leslie Alexander agreed.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think he's one of the greatest who ever played the game,''
Alexander said. ``He is a great player, but he also made the game
fun. People love to be around Charles, and an attitude like that is
rare in any sport. His routine will be missed.''
</P>
<P>
   Especially his routine on the court.
</P>
<P>
   A 6-6 power forward, Barkley averaged less than 10 rebounds only
once, when he averaged 8.6 as a rookie with the Philadelphia 76ers
in the 1984-85 season. Entering this season, Barkley has scored
23,468 points (13th on the all-time scoring list) and pulled down
12,337 rebounds, once leading the league (14.6 in 1986-87) and
hauling in a career-high 33 in his first game as a Rocket.
</P>
<P>
   Barkley averaged 12.3 rebounds last season, second in the NBA.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's a guy who's had a tremendous career and has done some
unbelievable things for his height,'' said Rockets coach Rudy
Tomjanovich. ``He's dominated the game at times _ at whatever his
true height is _ at the power forward position.''
</P>
<P>
   Taken out of Auburn by Philadelphia with the fifth pick in the
1984 draft, Barkley spent eight seasons with the 76ers before being
traded to Phoenix before the 1992-93 season. He was named the
league's Most Valuable Player in 1993 and has been selected
first-team All-NBA five times and second-team five times. He was
named to the NBA's 50 Greatest Players List.
</P>
<P>
   The one knock against Barkley has been he has not won an NBA
championship. Contemporaries such as Jordan, Bird, Johnson and
Olajuwon have won multiple titles; Barkley has made it to the NBA
Finals just once, in 1993, when the Suns lost to the Bulls in six
games, despite Barkley's averages of 27.3 points, 13 rebounds and
5.5 assists.
</P>
<P>
   Barkley was traded to the Rockets prior to the 1996-97 season
for Sam Cassell, Robert Horry, Mark Bryant and Chucky Brown. The
Rockets advanced to the Western Conference finals that season,
losing to the Utah Jazz in six games.
</P>
<P>
   Though he has no championship rings, Tomjanovich said Barkley's
legacy should not be that of a loser.
</P>
<P>
   ``There are a lot of guys in the league who have not won
championships,'' Tomjanovich said. ``But I'll bet that if you look
at the teams he's been on, their winning percentage is very high.
And there's a lot of great players who haven't won (a title).
</P>
<P>
   ``There are two in Utah (John Stockton and Karl Malone) who have
been around and have been all-pros, and there's one in New York
(Patrick Ewing) who comes to mind. And (the Lakers') Shaquille
(O'Neal), too. I think that (labeling Barkley a loser) is unfair.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think he came here and showed that he wants to win. He
really showed that in his actions _ the sacrifice he made to get
Scottie (Pippen) here (signing to play for the minimum so the
Rockets could take on Pippen's $67 million contract). I don't know
how many guys would do that.''
</P>
<P>
   Alexander, who said he was not surprised by the decision, is
happy to have Barkley play his last game as a Rocket.
</P>
<P>
   ``Definitely,'' Alexander said. ``It's nice to have a great one
retire in your uniform. And he's one of the greatest of all time.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
